<br>
A wailing could be heard throughout the hog farmstead beside the monastery.<br>
<br>
Brother McHearn looked up from his study.  ‘What is God’s sweet name was that??’<br>
He jumped to his feet and ran to the stained glass window, only to peer out through a myriad of color to the pasture.  Nothing looked amiss in dawn’s early glow, but surely he was not hearing things.  He grabbed up his robe and pulling it about himself he ran down the rough hewn stone stairway and out into the fields.<br>
<br>
The sound was startling.  Generally the monastery was quiet as the brother’s took a very solemn oath of silence.  He knew that if the sound persisted he would receive reports of the likes of “Banshee’s broke my study!” , “Evil is abroad in the sanctuary, Father!”, and of course “Screams like that!  Can only come from eating Ye’ Ole’ Taco Bell.”  He’d have a stack of papyrus three measures high on his mahogany desk to sort through and turn into the Main Branch of the Diocese in Camelot.. And those Bishops can be soooo stuffy.<br>
<br>
He saw a small bundle in the middle of the corral, and several newly awakened hogs eying it tentatively.  He knew if he didn’t get to it, whatever IT was, then there’d be a quick breaking-of-fast for the piggies.<br>
<br>
He jumped the wooden fence that kept the swine from becoming strays, hence leading to yet another stack of reports, and muttered the Friar’s version of an obscenity (Big fat pink clouds and midgets with fire-setting tendancies!) when he realized he forgot to don his slippers, and plunged ankle deep into mud and other less pleasant things one can find in a sty.<br>
<br>
Wading through the… uhm.. muck, he came to the bundle and picked it up.  Unwrapping it he looked upon the infant face of a boy, blonde haired and blue eyed, and coincidentally, large mouthed, which explained the vast amount of screaming.  Not knowing what to do and having absolutely zero experience in this sort of  “fatherhood”, he replaced the wrapping over the child’s face to muffle the cries and trodded back to the carved granite abbey.<br>
<br>
He quickly made his way through the gate and set the package, (now thankfully quieting down!) on the ground.  He looked up to the resident hunchback in the bell tower and made a series of gestures.  His right hand tugged his right earlobe twice.  His left hand grabbed at the end of his nose.  The right elbow waved in front of him in a circular motion while he hopped about of his left foot and spit.  Twice.  He could see the misshapen figure wave from its vantage point acknowledging the command.  As the friar scooped his burden back into his arms, the large brass bell rang clearly across the air one time, signaling a King’s Friar’s Convention, of KFC as they affectionately referred to it.  Making his way inside and to the washroom, Brother McHearn thought ‘There really has to be an easier way to dictate that the bell should ring once, and once only.”<br>
